## 2. `kernel/src/boot_image/mod.rs` runtime parser

Replace the `VM_ELF` static with the archive + a zero-alloc `no_std` view.

```rust
pub mod elf;

/// The packed MXBI archive of all boot-server ELFs, embedded by build.rs.
static BOOT_IMAGE: &[u8] = include_bytes!(env!("BOOT_IMAGE_PATH"));

const MXBI_MAGIC: u32 = 0x4942_584D;
const HDR_LEN: usize = 16;
const REC_LEN: usize = 32;
const NAME_LEN: usize = 20;

/// Zero-copy view over the embedded archive. All reads explicit LE
/// (`from_le_bytes`) — the bytes carry no alignment guarantee, exactly like elf.rs.
pub struct BootImage { bytes: &'static [u8] }

impl BootImage {
    /// Borrow the embedded archive. Validates magic/version; panics at boot on
    /// a malformed image (our own build produced it — any failure is a build bug,
    /// same fatal-at-boot policy as elf.rs).
    pub fn get() -> Self { /* check magic, version==1, entry_count fits */ }

    fn entry_count(&self) -> usize { /* rd_u32(8) */ }
    fn record(&self, i: usize) -> (i32 /*proc_nr*/, u32 /*off*/, u32 /*len*/, &'static [u8] /*name*/);

    /// ELF payload for a boot proc number, or None.
    pub fn module_by_proc_nr(&self, nr: ProcNr) -> Option<&'static [u8]>;

    /// ELF payload for a server name (e.g. "vfs"); reused by exec in slice 4.7.
    /// Compares against the NUL-trimmed record name.
    pub fn module_by_name(&self, name: &str) -> Option<&'static [u8]>;

    /// Iterate (proc_nr, name, elf) for the load loop. Returns an iterator that
    /// yields each record's decoded fields — implemented as a small index-based
    /// struct iterator (no alloc).
    pub fn iter(&self) -> BootImageIter<'static>;
}
```

Implementation notes:
- Reuse the `rd_u16`/`rd_u32`/`rd_u64` LE-helper idiom from `elf.rs` (either duplicate the two tiny helpers locally or lift them to a shared `pub(crate)` in `elf.rs`; duplicating `rd_u32` is cheapest and keeps `elf.rs` untouched).
- `name` decode: find first NUL in the 20-byte field, `core::str::from_utf8(...).ok()` of the prefix; compare in `module_by_name`. `ProcNr` lookup compares `rd_i32(rec+0) == nr.get()`.
- `module_by_proc_nr` takes `ProcNr` (matches the kernel's pervasive `ProcNr` type); `proc_nr` field stored as raw `i32`.
- No `alloc`. The iterator holds `(&BootImage view, idx)` and decodes on each `next()`.

